      <h1>Finding 8 confirmed</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Day 8 · JWT alg:none / Algorithm Confusion</p>
      <div class="flag-badge"><%= flag %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-grid">
      <div class="learn-card skill-card">
        <div class="card-icon">📚</div>
        <h2>The vulnerability</h2>
        <h3>Trusting the token's own header</h3>
        <p>A JWT's header tells the verifier which algorithm to use. If the verifier obeys that header without pinning, an attacker picks the algorithm. Including <code>none</code> (no signature) or downgrading from RS256 (asymmetric) to HS256 with the public key as the HMAC secret.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card world-card">
        <div class="card-icon">📰</div>
        <h2>Seen in the wild</h2>
        <h3>Auth0, Atlassian, more</h3>
        <p>Auth0's library shipped <code>alg:none</code>-acceptable verification by default. Atlassian was vulnerable. Most early JWT libraries had this footgun. CVEs in this class still surface yearly. Every new language's JWT library rediscovers the bug.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card career-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🛠️</div>
        <h2>How to fix it</h2>
        <h3>Pin the algorithm server-side</h3>
        <p><code>jwt.verify(token, secret, { algorithms: ['HS256'] })</code>. Pass the algorithm allow-list explicitly. Never derive it from the token's own header. Reject <code>none</code>, reject mismatches, reject unknown algs. Treat the token's header as data, not as a directive.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card key-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔑</div>
        <h2>One-line takeaway</h2>
        <h3>Attacker-controlled fields are never directives</h3>
        <p>Same pattern as SSRF (attacker picks the URL), prompt injection (attacker picks the instructions), and SQLi (attacker picks the syntax). Anywhere your code reads an attacker-controlled value and uses it to choose <em>what to do</em>, you have a class of bug to hunt for.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="completion-banner">
      <div class="completion-stars">🏆</div>
